annotationA: Probable prefoldin subunit 5; Binds specifically to cytosolic chaperonin (c-CPN) and transfers target proteins to it. Binds to nascent polypeptide chain and promotes folding in an environment in which there are many competing pathways for nonnative proteins (By similarity)
annotationB: 28S ribosomal protein S7, mitochondrial; Structural constituent of ribosome; RNA binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: translation; Belongs to the universal ribosomal protein uS7 family
